Iavan Pijoos, News24(ER24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Polokwane - Four people were killed and five injured when two vehicles collided head-on on the R71 in Polokwane, Limpopo, on Monday, paramedics said.A bakkie and a light delivery vehicle collided around 17:00, ER24 said in a statement.The injured included a man believed to be in his late twenties, who sustained a head injury, and a woman in her thirties, who sustained pelvic fractures.No further details were immediately available. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.